@deffn Function gtk-drag-dest-find-target  (self@tie{}@code{<gtk-widget>}) (context@tie{}@code{<gdk-drag-context>}) (target_list@tie{}@code{<gtk-target-list*>}) @result{}@tie{} (ret@tie{}@code{<gdk-atom>})
Looks for a match between @var{context->targets} and the @var{dest-target-list},
returning the first matching target, otherwise returning @samp{GDK_NONE}.
@var{dest-target-list} should usually be the return value from
@code{gtk-drag-dest-get-target-list}, but some widgets may have different valid
targets for different parts of the widget; in that case, they will have to
implement a drag_motion handler that passes the correct target list to this
function.

@table @var
@item widget
drag destination widget

@item context
drag context

@item target-list
list of droppable targets, or @samp{@code{#f}} to use
gtk_drag_dest_get_target_list (@var{widget}).

@item ret
first target that the source offers and the dest can accept, or @samp{GDK_NONE}

@end table

@end deffn

